content:
Sync Agent Presence Statuses Automatically

Let your contact centers automatically sync agentsâ€™ Omni-Channel presence statuses to indicate their availability to receive work. Reduce human error by clicking the Presence Status Sync button on your contact center to detect and restore out-of-sync statuses.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS:
Customize Application AND Manage Call Centers
Contact Center Admin
Customize Application AND Manage Call Centers
Contact Center Admin (Partner Telephony)

This feature is available with Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect, Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect, and Service Cloud Voice with Partner Telephony.

After you configure Omni-Channel for Voice, your contact center can sync agent presence statuses.

From Setup, in the Quick Find box, enter Contact Center. Select Amazon Contact Centers or Partner Telephony Contact Centers, depending on your telephony model.
Select the contact center to sync agent presence statuses with.
Click Presence Status Sync and then Save.

Configure Omni-Channel for Voice
Presence Status Settings
title: Automatically Sync Agent Presence Statuses in Service Cloud
